sentences.english: The captains report to the commandant that they are ready to accomplish their tasks.
sentences.chinese: 舰长向司令官汇报他们已经做好完成任务的准备。

sentences.english: Entering the navy as a volunteer, he served in the Dutch Wars and became post captain in 1673.
sentences.chinese: 他志愿参军，在英荷战争中成为上校舰长。

sentences.english: At two bells the captain came on deck.
sentences.chinese: 二击钟时舰长来到了甲板上。

sentences.english: He wanted to be Captain Kirk in Star Trek.
sentences.chinese: 他想要成为星际争霸战里的寇克舰长。

sentences.english: Skull Leader to Icarus. What's going on, Captain?
sentences.chinese: 骷髅中队长呼叫“伊卡洛斯”号。发生了什么，舰长？

sentences.english: The U-boat captains could hardly believe their good fortune.
sentences.chinese: 艇舰长们简直不敢相信他们的好运气。

sentences.english: The ship's captain commands all the officers and men.
sentences.chinese: 舰长统率舰上全体官兵。

sentences.english: Lisa: Captain, I can't reach to reach either the Daedelus or the Prometheus…
sentences.chinese: 舰长，我无法和普罗米修斯或者戴德拉思基地联系上。

sentences.english: Sorry Captain, your TriCorder is in Airplane Mode.
sentences.chinese: 对不起舰长，你的传送器开了飞行模式。

sentences.english: The captain and his lieutenant rushed to the companionway.
sentences.chinese: 舰长和海军上尉急忙冲到甲板梯口。

sentences.english: Which officer in the ship navigates ?
sentences.chinese: 舰长统率舰上全体官兵。

sentences.english: In the navy, a captain is above a commander.
sentences.chinese: 在海军中，舰长职位高于指挥官。

sentences.english: Muller, the German captain, decided to complete some repairs here.
sentences.chinese: 埃姆登号舰长穆勒决定在这里把船修理好。

sentences.english: Good luck on your new mission, Captain Grant.
sentences.chinese: 祝你在新任务中好运，格兰特舰长。

definition: junior ranking officer in Chinese army/major/lieutenant commander
middle ranking officer in Chinese army/lieutenant colonel/commander
high ranking officer in Chinese army/colonel
lieutenant commander (= UK and US Navy equivalent)
